Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.689 --> 00:00:04.689
&lt;&lt;Music&gt;&gt;

00:00:04.689 --> 00:00:06.809
&lt;&lt;Arizona Fight Song&gt;&gt;

00:00:06.809 --> 00:00:15.150
Jacqueline Mok: Welcome to this glorious July
day when we welcome the 21st president of

00:00:15.150 --> 00:00:21.620
the University of Arizona Ann Weaver Hart
and her husband Randy Hart.

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:22.850
Welcome!

00:00:22.850 --> 00:00:26.540
Zachary Brooks: Hello.

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.370
Welcome to campus President Hart.

00:00:29.370 --> 00:00:33.660
On behalf of the eight thousand five hundred
graduate and professional students of the

00:00:33.660 --> 00:00:37.070
University of Arizona I would like to welcome
you to campus.

00:00:37.070 --> 00:00:41.359
Krystina Nguyen: The students of this institution
are highly diverse, driven, and have remarkable

00:00:41.359 --> 00:00:43.870
wildcat spirit and pride, as I am sure you
probably already see.

00:00:43.870 --> 00:00:49.300
Dr. Hart: I am looking forward to meeting
all of you and joining together to help the

00:00:49.300 --> 00:00:54.920
future of this great institution be great
in the way it was in the past, but even better

00:00:54.920 --> 00:01:00.390
as we look to becoming and staying one of
the finest institutions in the world and fulfilling

00:01:00.390 --> 00:01:05.180
that incredibly important role in the broader
society and thank you for such a warm welcome.

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:07.280
I appreciate it very much.

00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:08.820
Thank you!

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:10.360
&lt;&lt;Applause&gt;&gt;

00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:16.550
Dr. Hart: I’m thrilled.

00:01:16.550 --> 00:01:23.750
This is such a welcome and to have everyone
come out in the Alumni Plaza and give me such

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:26.230
a warm welcome was very moving.

00:01:26.230 --> 00:01:30.790
I’ve been so anxious to get here that I
can hardly believe that day has finally arrived.

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:35.130
Zachary Brooks: Given the strong presence
the international students have on the graduate

00:01:35.130 --> 00:01:40.000
and professional programs I should finish
my welcome fitting my program and GPSC’s

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:49.030
people by saying welcome… (continues to
say welcome in different languages)

00:01:49.030 --> 00:01:50.410
… and of course welcome.

00:01:50.410 --> 00:01:53.130
Welcome to the University of Arizona.

00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:56.550
UA Employee: Thank you for stopping by.

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:59.480
It was nice to meet you.

00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:02.420
Dr. Hart: Oh it was wonderful.

00:02:02.420 --> 00:02:05.649
Enjoy your August I know it will be very,
very good.

